main event: A sighting of an unidentified aerial object was reported over Itazuke, Japan on January 18, 1956, described as resembling a project balloon.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of 40,000 feet and had no contrail., The object was classified as moving fast., A total of 19 objects were reported during the sighting., It was mentioned that the object was possibly a balloon., The observation lasted 45 seconds with a brief summary indicating the object's shape.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a project balloon
